Co louia Ruijsten & van Boun

11 ditto 1681
over Bode mijn steer Ambrosins Hertuys
Ick hebbe den ul van 6 deser wel ontf. als mede de Æ’509:- door
ul ordre van nist tlexandevigas en gevolghde quitantie aen hem daer
vangeven, waer over ul hertlijke bedancke ul versekerende vande
d 11 Ditto
groo te geneghent heyst
Bruggen mijn hr. Coots
mijnst. sedert den mijnen van 9 deser, den ul van selve dato bekomen John Collinur
heeft wel gedaen geen kanten mede te nemen, t geene andere oock wel souden doen
soo eenighe vreese hebben van outdeek & alsoo hobert for ul veel goets toeseght
soo gelieft hem het packie N.17 mede te geven, N.18. gaet heden op nieuwporte
en hope for oock haest sal vertreken, waer van een woort tot adviss: ul
tratos sal vereeren, en bij mankemente van tijt en hebbe ul Rek noch niet
gexamineert die aen mijne gissinge in debet ontvalt: verneme gerne Â£
thomas white int minste niet vernemt, midts die van london scryve
hij allanck van daer was verroke godt verleene alles te beste d'eenot
d'ander arviveerende doet als voor eggen Aen boort Joan Hrmoys is tot london
voor mij geladen een Engalsch pack perse bestaende in defferente stucken
daer over groot sorge gelieft te nemen, op dat geen boomen spillen schjven
ofte iyet dier gelijck wort geguelst ofte verloren gaet & mij met alle
sorge wort toe gesonden tis twee spillen & oper & onder werck mat
2 ysere stucken 4 lodges een groote & clejn handt boom a gonieno blijv
21 ditto 1681
meuwe port michiel vallego

@ 11 ditto 1681
Lille
Richd:. Southell
Sr. I have this week receaved 3 of yd one of 22 past. & of 6 & 8 curits
as for yd drawing, I could vere well digest, onely, because I promised you
to remitt & that you without any more draw, you could not be or finde
yd self the fristrated by my non complyance for you knew I wass att
Brussel to provide mony to the purpose butt no more of that because the
difference is onelj a mis understanding I have made no scruple in the least
to accept yd bill, butt gave itt all necessary know itt is indorsed to m.
van Ess mr. seamans landlord, which know boath you & mee, so beg
not concerned in the least, neither blame mee for grumbling, because
I had not yd advise which now come to hand with that of 6 curitt
where itt hath been detained I know not I am sorry that you feare
that yd naturalisition shall not answer yd purpose, yett I could advise
to venter the case, because yd freinds will engage that itt shall pass
the seale, so, into one butt itt will be inregistred: which in case nt
that you do not thingck yd self secure enough without itt you will
do well to choose best, butt att Lille you are now settled & accquainted
which perhaps should cost you boath mony & greath paines to be alle
where except you I could finde conveniency att hambourgh as formearly
you proposed where in I can serve you, you may depend up on my utmost
endeavours to promote yd intrest wee apprehend no warre between
france & England butt to contrary with france & as because the
king doth continew new pretentions & maintaines not the articles
of please, as the news is here so in case any rupture itt will be yett
worse with us for nothwithstanding wee have a verey inconsiderable
trade yett others are geallow & will be of our intrest, in som
that 3 new ware houses are sett up, besides that the heares of dumont
do maintaine theirs, I say ware houses of cloth so there is the less hope to
promote & advance bij our selling here the bill I shall send you next tuesday
my freind being yett this day here exspected & so remaine
Antwerpen 12 July
London Michiel Peeters
mons. 5 deser heb aen ul wat noot sakelijk was gescreven, sedert den ul van 2
passato bekomen: ul lakens moeten costij verkoght worden, en doet debvoor
r. slaughter daer toe te bewegen dat hijse wederneemt al wast tot 20 P
verlies, want vande geilcoleuren en kan ick int minst geen gelt makens ul
Broeder schrijft dat ick Æ’1000: in cassa hadde, ende dat ul een ordre hebt
gegeven aen mr slaught om deselve aen hem betalen: daer heeft ul qualijk in
gedaen, want gij en sult van hem dan geen genegentheyt vinden tot de lakens
maer hij sal continueeren om u te presteren tot betaling van d'ander reste soo
is, daer niet anders aen te doen, dan dat hij de lakens weder nemt volgens ul
sal accordeeren ende dat men hem de reste op leght in gelt tot volle betalinghe
d
d'welke als wanneer geschiet, over mijne rekeninge verstaen een advistement
te hebben, oversulx soo haest ul mat mr. slanghter over een komt, soo
belieft aen ul broeder Antoni een volle procuratie te senden om mij te
dischargeren van alles waermede nae graet
@ 12 ditto 1681
London William Scawen
th
Sr. I have recd. in due time yd of 1
past. as for our callicoes
butt vere few, because the bales of long cloth prove so cours & bad that when
wee have yett butt small
sale, besides the bales of long cloth prove well 10 p.. worse then the formars, &
can herdely sell y the dyed salempores are ill conditioned, full of holes within
I sold yesterday 50 peeces, & have been obliged to take y. all againe, because att
the opening of 5 or 6 they were all faulty, so they would not keep the rest
the mulmus will not sell att all because the hollands is much finer & better
the duagares are to cours forour markett, so I doubt I shall have much a do
to putt off most and or all before next sale: when you have any mony for
mee please te pay itt to mr. maynard & advise mee: tijkes are risen here because
thread is risen neare is p yesterday i pay 10 stivers a peece for each sort
more then here before, so you please to governe yd self accordingly whilst I remain
Lile
London nam Lury knightley
@ 12 ditto 1681
dck
Sr. I have before mee boath yd of 17 & 23: past with the accounpt of 5 dubble
to
reds & one bay in the bale N.7: ams. to Â£57:3 with the charges of packing
& brok. which you have valuwed on mee att 2 uso in yd bill for Â£150 & that
I should pass Â£92:17 to acctt. of HC. which I have accepted accordingly & past
to booke â€” I observe what you say of GN silver: I have no correspondency
with John kent, butt I know he sends them to one of his correspondents
here, from which our Jesuits take 20 or 30 & some times more cloathes
a yeare & that I desired them silver marcks is because the Jesuits have
promised mee to take them from mee in case I could deliver them the
right marck & sort and as yett I have not had any butt you say he hath
now 5p. underhand which if were ready in london, that I could have
them in 2 or 3 weekes could yett serve mee, so please to do mee
the favour to procure them if possible whilst in all occasions you will
besure to finde mee
a u 12 ditto 1681
London Abram vivian
Sr. mij last to you was on the 5:h curitt sence recd. yd of 24 past tis wel you have
orders to finish the last desired pack in closed are pattarnes for one pack of fine
northrens, which please to order mr. potter to provide for as yett I approve of
his doing, recommend, him the grayes that they be exactely to the pattarnes
mr. lively hood & cullours, & that he doth his utmost endeavour to compleat
this pack to the orders pr yd next I hope to understand how you shipped
the good att Hull John nelson is now there & I supose he will be ready as soone
as pindar for I know there is much butter & severall packs ready to ship
aboard of him to gett him awaij before pindar yett, so do yd endeavour
to divert our risico & to have some goods aboard of each, of which thought
